# Design Alternatives

In designing a database schema, we must ensure that we avoid two major
pitfalls

- **1. Redundancy** 
  - storing the same information multiple times unnecessarily.
  - Normalization solves this by separating entities and linking them with IDs.

| offering_id | course_id | course_title                | semester    |
| ----------- | --------- | --------------------------- | ----------- |
| 1           | CS101     | Introduction to Programming | Fall 2025   |
| 2           | CS101     | Introduction to Programming | Spring 2026 |
| 3           | CS101     | Introduction to Programming | Fall 2026   |


- **2. Incompletness**
  - Here Incompletness refer the NULL Introduced due to adding new information or data in table.
  
| offering_id | course_id | course_title    | semester |
| ----------- | --------- | --------------- | -------- |
| NULL        | CS205     | Data Structures | NULL     |


